                       "options":  {
                                       "content":  "Use this dashboard for bounded operational log inspection only.\n\n- Indexed Loki labels are limited to `service`, `level`, and `event`.\n- `requestId`, `traceId`, and `spanId` remain JSON body fields and are not dashboard variables or Loki labels.\n- For correlation searches, open the Loki datasource in Grafana Explore, retain a bounded service selector, use a short time range, and add a body filter such as `{service=\"api-gateway\"} |= \"\u003crequestId\u003e\"`.\n- Do not search for or expose API keys, JWTs, authorization headers, cookies, request bodies, response bodies, database URLs, Redis credentials, Secret values, raw exception objects, or arbitrary header maps.\n- Logs are operational evidence only. They are not authentication, authorization, quota, billing, analytics, routing, health-registry, or audit sources of truth.",
